            https://eloquentjavascript.net/04_data.html

        - Do Javascript 30: Day 04 Array Cardio
            https://javascript30.com/

        - Do a minimum of 1, 8 kyu Fundamentals on CodeWars EVERY DAY. Spend at least 20 minutes trying to solve it before looking at the solution.

Notes:

   Name arrays plurally

   Get array length
       const movies = ["The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting"];
       console.log(movies.length); // 3

    Access an element
        const movies = ["The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting"];
        console.log(movies[0]); // "The Wolf of Wall Street"
        console.log(movies[1]); // "Zootopia"
        console.log(movies[2]); // "Babysitting"

    Iterate with for loop

        const movies = ["The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting"];
        for (let i = 0; i < movies.length; i++) {
            console.log(movies[i]);
        }


    Iterate with for each function

        const movies = ["The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting"];
        movies.forEach(movie => { console.log(movie); });


    Add to array (end)

        const movies = ["The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting"];
        movies.push("Ghostbusters");
        console.log(movies) // "The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting", "Ghostbusters"

    Add to array (start)

        const movies = ["The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting"];
        movies.unshift("Pacific Rim");
        console.log(movies) // "Pacific Rim", "The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting"

    Remove element (last value)
        const movies = ["The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting"];
        movies.pop(); // Remove the last array element

    Remove element (specific)
        const movies = ["The Wolf of Wall Street", "Zootopia", "Babysitting"];
        movies.splice(0, 1); // Remove 1 element starting at index 0
        console.log(movies.length); // 2
        console.log(movies[0]); // "Zootopia"
        console.log(movies[1]); // "Babysitting"



